# Git Commit Conventions

This project MUST show clean, incremental development history for the beecrowd/Winter
assessment. Never squash the entire implementation into one commit.

## When to commit

- Commit only when the user explicitly asks (e.g. "commit T010-T011").
- After completing a **checkpoint** in `specs/001-ai-order-engine/tasks.md`, suggest a commit.
- One logical unit per commit: setup slice, schema, tests, service, routes, or docs.
- Do NOT commit unrelated phases together (e.g. orders API + AI chat in one commit).

## Message format (Conventional Commits)

```text
<type>(<scope>): <imperative summary ≤72 chars>

Refs: T0XX[-T0YY]
```

**Types**: `feat` | `test` | `chore` | `docs` | `fix` | `refactor`

**Language**: English for commit subjects.

**Examples**:

```text
chore(setup): scaffold Next.js 15 App Router project
Refs: T001

feat(orders): implement POST and GET /api/orders endpoints
Refs: T025-T026

test(cancel): add integration tests for PENDING-only cancellation
Refs: T027-T028
```

## Suggested commit map (follow during implementation)

| Phase | Suggested commits | Tasks |
|-------|-------------------|-------|
| Setup | scaffold + deps; docker compose; assets + layout | T001-T009 |
| Foundational | prisma schema + migration; lib clients + lock; services skeleton + schema tests; instrumentation | T010-T019 |
| US1 | order tests; order service; order API routes | T020-T026 |
| US2 | cancel tests; cancel service + route | T027-T030 |
| US3 | batch tests; batch service + cron; trigger route + logging | T031-T037 |
| US4 | chat tool tests; KB + tools + agent; chat API + UI | T038-T045 |
| Polish | swagger asset; README SDD + GenAI; gitignore + validation fixes | T046-T052 |

Prefer **test commit before feat** when TDD applies (e.g. T020 before T022).

## Files to NEVER commit

`.env`, secrets, `node_modules/`, `.next/`, local IDE config with credentials.

## After committing

Run `git status` to confirm a clean working tree for the completed slice before
starting the next phase.
